reviewText: I love just about everything Norah Jones does including this dvd. I think she sounded good, and I don't think the dvd was too dark in places. But because I gave this dvd 4 stars instead of 5 stars was because of her nasty comment to the audience after she sang Rosie's Lullaby. The audience clapped their hands and she snapped at them as if they did not like the song. I guess she wanted then to jump for joy or something, I don't really know why she reacted that way to them. I still will continue to buy most of her cd's and dvd's however.
summary: Norah pleases her audience once again

reviewText: I saw Norah in a recent concert on tv and wanted to hear more.  I was glad to find other dvd's of her concerts.  She is an amazing musician.  She has a way of capturing your attention and drawing one into her songs.  People who know Norah will love this and people who haven't heard her, do yourselves a favor and listen.

reviewText: This is a very good concert, by Norah & her band. This was filmed on June 14, 2007. It has an approximate running time of 76 minutes. Most of the songs were written by Norah, herself. Norah was born in New York, raised in Dallas, Texas, and now lives in New York. Norah went to music school, while growing up in Dallas.The line-up:Norah Jones - vocals, piano, guitarLee Alexander - bass, vocals, lap steelAndrew Borger - drums, percussion, marimba]Adam Levy - guitar, banjo, vocalsDaru Oda - alto flute, bass, harmonica, percussion, piano, & vocalsSpecial Guests:M.Ward - guitar, vocalsJ.Walter Hawkes - tromboneThe song set:1.Come Away with me2.Those Sweet Words3.The Sun Doesn't like You4.Not my Friend5.Thinking About You6.Be my Somebody7.Rosie's Lullaby8.Sunrise9.Sinkin' Soon10.No too Late11.My Dear Country12.Little Room13.Broken14.Long Way Home15.Creepin' In16.Hands on the Wheel17.Blue Bayou (written by Roy Orbison, a native Texan)18.Don't Know WhyOverall, this is a very good concert. Thanks!!!!

reviewText: This is certainly my least favorite of the 3 Norah Jones DVDs I have.  The playing isn't as good as the second DVD.  Watching Adam Levy the guitarist is always a bit painful since he's not really a solid improviser or fits in with songs that are more country bases.  I do give it to him that his improvisation skills have improved a bit.  The performance wasn't very exciting.......
summary: Not as good as the other 2 DVDs
